        <num>CC 3025</num>
        <heading>3025.  Termination by principal</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3025.  Termination by principal
The principal may terminate the mandate and the authority of the mandatary at any
time.  A mandate in the interest of the principal, and also of the mandatary or of a third
person, may be irrevocable, if the parties so agree, for as long as the object of the contract
may require.</p>
        </content>
